Find { \mathbf a \cdot \mathbf b } 
      if \left| {\mathbf a} \right| = 8, \left| {\mathbf b} \right| = 3,
      and the angle between {\mathbf a} and {\mathbf b} is 
      \frac{\pi}{9} radians.

Find { \mathbf a \cdot \mathbf b } 
      if \left| {\mathbf a} \right| = 10, \left| {\mathbf b} \right| = 6,
      and the angle between {\mathbf a} and {\mathbf b} is 
      \frac{\pi}{6} radians.

\bf{a} \times \bf{b}= \bf{i} + 
       \bf{j} + 
       \bf{k}

\mathbf{i} + 
      \mathbf{j} +
      \mathbf{k}

static.solution:







The area of the triangle is half of the area of the parallelogram determined by the vectors \vec{OP}=\left\lt 0,7,4\right> and \vec{OQ}=\left\lt 0,5,6\right>. Thus,



S=\frac{1}{2} || \vec{OP} \times \vec{OQ} ||



We compute the cross product:



\vec{OP} \times \vec{OQ}=
\left| \begin{array}{ccc}
 \boldsymbol{i} \amp  \boldsymbol{j} \amp  \boldsymbol{k} \\
 0 \amp  7 \amp  4 \\
 0 \amp  5 \amp  6
\end{array} \right|
= 
  \left| \begin{array}{cc} 7 \amp  4 \\ 5 \amp  6 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{i}
- \left| \begin{array}{cc} 0 \amp  4 \\ 0 \amp  6 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{j}
+ \left| \begin{array}{cc} 0 \amp  7 \\ 0 \amp  5 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{k} 


\qquad = 22 \boldsymbol{i} + 0 \boldsymbol{j} + 0 \boldsymbol{k}



S=\frac{1}{2}|| 22 \boldsymbol{i} + 0 \boldsymbol{j} + 0 \boldsymbol{k} ||
   =\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{(22)^2+(0)^2+(0)^2}
   \approx 11.

